UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1971
1 AN ACT proposing to create a new section of the Constitution of Kentucky relating
2 to property exempt from taxation.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 Section 1. Are you in favor of exempting from state and local property taxes the
5 permanent residence and primary motor vehicle of an owner who is a 100% disabled
6 veteran from the United States Armed Forces or an unremarried surviving spouse of a
7 United States Armed Forces service member killed in action while performing active
8 military duty by amending the Constitution of Kentucky to read as stated below?
9 SECTION 2. IT IS PROPOSED THAT A NEW SECTION BE ADDED TO
10 THE CONSTITUTION OF KENTUCKY TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
11 There shall be exempt from taxation real property of less than one hundred acres
12 maintained solely as the primary permanent residence and personal property of a
13 motor vehicle maintained solely as a primary motor vehicle of an owner who is:
14 (1) A veteran of the United States Armed Forces with a one hundred percent
15 service-connected disability rating; or
16 (2) A surviving spouse of a United States Armed Forces member killed in
17 action while performing active military duty, who did not remarry after the member's
18 death.
19 To receive an exemption under this section, the owner shall file with the
20 appropriate local assessor by December 31 of the taxation period, on forms provided
21 therefor, a signed statement, made under penalty of perjury, indicating his or her
22 eligibility for the exemption and submit the proper documentation for substantiation.
23 Section 3. This amendment shall be submitted to the voters of the
24 Commonwealth for their ratification or rejection at the time and in the manner provided
25 for under Sections 256 and 257 of the Constitution, KRS 118.415, and Sections 4 and 5
26 of this Act.
27 Section 4. Notwithstanding any provision of KRS 118.415 to the contrary, the
